ated color theory into hundred-square grids sampling everything from mummy cases to butterfly wings. Long overlooked, the book is now read as anticipating Klee, Albers, and Rothko by decades.","number":2},{"category":"social_reform","header":"She remade Litchfield in Colonial Revival","body":"As curator of the Litchfield Historical Society, Vanderpoel drove the town's Colonial Revival, behind the restorations of the Congregational Church and the Litchfield Law School. She also helped found the local DAR chapter named for her great-grandmother Mary Floyd Tallmadge.","number":3},{"category":"legacy","header":"She finished her son's gift to Litchfield","body":"When her son John Arent died with his library building unfinished, Emily completed the project and set a memorial tablet to him beneath its Palladian window. The building honored her mother, Julia Tallmadge Noyes.","number":4}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[{"artwork_id":"ART082","role":"creator"}],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X03136","display_label":"her father-in-law, Congressman Aaron Vanderpoel"},{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD3004","display_label":"led Hartford's preservation as Vanderpoel did Litchfield's"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Emily Caroline","last_name":"Noyes","display_name":"Emily Caroline Noyes Vanderpoel","gender":"female","married_names":["Vanderpoel"],"maiden_name":"Noyes","bio_blurb":"Artist and author of \"Chronicles of a Pioneer School\"","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780940427/Photo_of_Emily_Noyes_Vanderpoel_excifx.jpg"},"military_service":[],"career":[],"birth":{"year":1842,"country":"United States","city":"New York","state":"New York"},"death":{"year":1939,"country":"United States","city":"New York","state":"New York"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM749"},"education":[],"slug":"emily-caroline-noyes-1842"}},"burial